profile_positions.description:
Acted as the UNFPA Turkey Cross-Border Program M&E and information management officer. The main tasks performed under this role have been:

Monitoring and Evaluation
- Leading third party monitoring activities; 
- Updating office monitoring systems to meet UNFPA and WoS requirements; 
- Data verification and analysis for the program to identify emerging trends and areas of improvement; 
- Quarterly data review meetings with IPs; 

Information Management
- Updating information management protocols for the office; 
- Managing data and information management systems for feeding into program strategies, monitoring activities, funding processes as well as reporting cycles;   

Reporting
- Donor reporting for DIFID, ECHO, Canada and OFDA projects; 
- Reporting on SIS and humanitarian fact-sheet, 
- Monthly situational reports and GBV 4Ws reporting 
- Coaching and support to implementing partners on data reporting and information management.

Program Support
- Supporting the development and review of project log-frames for implementing partners; 
- Supporting the calculation of IP and internal WP indicators
